<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-03T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-03T14:00:00-05:00" n="127" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d127">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/7137: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate
                                    Peace</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extracts]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-03T20:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">October 3,
                                        1919, 8 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received October 4, 3:35
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>4503. Council of the Heads of Delegations met Thursday morning, October
                            2d.</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                        <p>6. With regard to the method of communicating the decision of the Council
                            regarding the blockade of Soviet Russia to neutral governments, the
                            Council decided that Mr. <persName corresp="#p_CGEB1">Clemenceau</persName> as President of the Peace Conference should
                            address a note to the diplomatic representatives of the neutral powers
                            at Paris.</p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_PFL"><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></persName></signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Mission</hi></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>